    • Method Detail

      • setupPaydiantApplicationConfig

        public void setupPaydiantApplicationConfig(String host,
                                  String protocol,
                                  ContextWrapper contextWrapper,
                                  byte[] appSignature,
                                  byte[] apiKey)
        Initializes the Paydiant SDK with the provided appSignature value.

        Note: DO NOT specify appSignature using the string value (i.e., "app-signature".getBytes()), as the string values would be easier to lookup.
        Parameters:
        host - the host
        protocol - the protocol
        contextWrapper - Android ContextWrapper instance
        appSignature - App Signature associated with this app.
        apiKey - API key associated with this app

      • setupPaydiantApplicationConfig

        public void setupPaydiantApplicationConfig(String host,
                                  String protocol,
                                  ContextWrapper contextWrapper,
                                  byte[] appSignature,
                                  byte[] apiKey,
                                  Properties paydaintSDKConfigProps)
        Initializes the SDK using the custom properties provided through the paydaintSDKConfigProps parameter. Properties provided through the paydaintSDKConfigProps parameter can be used to change some of the default behaviors like disabling hashing for the password/pin. Currently supported property keys for this would be;
        • PASSWORD_ENCRYPTION_KEY
        • PASSCODE_ENCRYPTION_KEY
        • MFA_ANSWER_ENCRYPTION_KEY
        • MFA_ANSWER_CASE_SENSITIVITY_KEY


        Note: DO NOT specify appSignature using the string value (i.e., "app-signature".getBytes()), as the string values would be easier to lookup.
        Parameters:
        host - host
        protocol - protocol (http or https)
        contextWrapper - Android ContextWrapper instance
        appSignature - App Signature associated with this app.
        paydaintSDKConfigProps - Properties to change the default behavior of the SDK.
        apiKey - API key associated with this app

      • isEncryptMFAAnswer

        public boolean isEncryptMFAAnswer()
        Checks if the MFA answer needs to be encrypted or not. Defaults to true, unless otherwise overridden by the MFA_ANSWER_ENCRYPTION_KEY is set using the properties of setupPaydiantApplicationConfig(String, String, ContextWrapper, byte[], byte[], Properties)
        Returns:
        true, if MFA answer needs to be encrypted or not.
        Since:
        4.3.0.3

      • isMfaAnswerCaseSensitive

        public boolean isMfaAnswerCaseSensitive()
        Checks whether the MFA answer needs to be case-sensitive or not. For MFA answers that are case-insensitive will be converted to lower case. This defaults to false and can be overridden using the MFA_ANSWER_CASE_SENSITIVITY_KEY configuration property.
        Returns:
        whether the MFA answer needs to be case sensitive or not.
        Since:
        4.4.0.2
